==English==

===Etymology===
[[Ancient Greek]] (krithomanteia), "divination by barley" < (krithe), "barley"

===Alternative Spellings===
*[[critomancy]]
*[[krithomancy]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# [[divination]] by interpreting food, usually bread and grain used in sacrifice.

